  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Postprandial glycaemic control is an important risk factor for the development of type 2
      diabetes, cardiovascular disease and all-cause mortality.

      Previous research has demonstrated that exercise performed in the postprandial state
      paradoxically results in a deterioration in glucose tolerance in the immediate post-exercise
      period (Gonzalez et a. 2013; Gonzalez and Stevenson 2013). This study aims to assess the
      timecourse of this post-exercise effect.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
